The '''Sulawesi heleia''' ('''''Heleia squamiceps'''''), also known as the '''streaky-headed white-eye''' and '''streak-headed ibon''',<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldbirdnames.org/new/ioc-lists/master-list-2/ |title=Master Lists: v15.1 |website=[[IOC World Bird List]] |publisher=[[International Ornithologists' Union]] |access-date=13 March 2025}}</ref> is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Zosteropidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Sulawesi]], [[Indonesia]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]].

